SUMMARY:Boca do Rio Live at Morgan’s Mill
DESCRIPTION:Boca do Rio Live at Morgan’s Mill – Friday\, March 13 \nLeft of the Dial Promotions presents Boca do Rio\, live at Morgan’s Mill in Woodland on Friday\, March 13 from 6–8 PM. Born as a bossa nova trio in 1999\, Boca do Rio has evolved into a high-energy electro-funk ensemble blending traditional Brazilian rhythms with contemporary Bay Area grooves. Based in Davis\, the band delivers a vibrant\, danceable sound that’s both rooted and forward-thinking. \nThis free\, all-ages show invites the community to experience a night of rhythmic exploration\, soulful melodies\, and global fusion in an intimate café setting. \nVenue: Morgan’s Mill – 262 East St\, Woodland\, CA\nTime: 6:00–8:00 PM\nAdmission: Free | All Ages
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/boca-do-rio-live-at-morgans-mill/
LOCATION:Morgan’s Mill\, 1059 Court St.\, Woodland\, CA\, 95695-9112\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/images-5.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Left of the Dial Promotions":MAILTO:leftofthedialpromotions@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
